 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.344","title":"[audit][io][tls] Preserve TLS half-close semantics in TlsStream shutdown","description":"TlsStream conflated local write shutdown and peer EOF into a full Closed tombstone, which let copy_bidirectional() and other duplex flows truncate the reverse direction. Scope: keep local shutdown write-only until peer EOF, preserve writes after peer EOF until local close_notify, and add regression coverage in TLS conformance tests.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"RubyCreek","created_at":"2026-03-13T06:41:28.264767102Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T06:41:53.804678258Z","closed_at":"2026-03-13T06:41:53.804656487Z","close_reason":"Completed: TlsStream now preserves duplex half-close semantics by separating local write shutdown from peer read EOF, and TLS conformance regressions cover eventual close plus continued reads after local shutdown. Validation: rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-tls-336-test-feature cargo test --test tls_conformance --features tls -- --nocapture compiled and both affected tests passed; rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-tls-336-check cargo check --all-targets --features tls passed aside from unrelated existing gen_server warning; rustfmt +nightly --edition 2024 --check src/tls/stream.rs tests/tls_conformance.rs passed; rch exec -- cargo fmt --check and rch exec -- env CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/tmp/rch-tls-336-clippy cargo clippy --all-targets --features tls -- -D warnings remain blocked by unrelated existing workspace drift/debt.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.344","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T06:41:28.264767102Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.345","title":"[audit] Fresh-eyes batch 340: 66 files 100-291L range, all small modules","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T06:45:30.171454035Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T06:45:57.717308158Z","closed_at":"2026-03-13T06:45:57.717278743Z","close_reason":"All 66 files SOUND across ~11,500 lines. Zero bugs. Files ranged 100-291L including fs/read_dir, codec/lines, error/recovery, record/finalizer, runtime/yield_now, stream/fuse, signal/ctrl_c, lib.rs and many more.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.345","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T06:45:30.171454035Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.346","title":"[audit][websocket] Make WebSocket::close use explicit Cx time source","description":"src/net/websocket/client.rs::WebSocket::close still tries to derive handshake timeout timestamps from an ambient current context path that no longer exists in the workspace frontier, which shows up as compile errors at the close-handshake clock reads. Scope: make close() use the explicit &Cx timer driver / wall-clock fallback consistently for initial deadline and loop timeout checks, keep behavior deterministic, and validate with rch-offloaded targeted tests/checks where the shared frontier allows.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"DarkBadger","created_at":"2026-03-13T06:50:34.840113849Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T07:00:13.507057670Z","closed_at":"2026-03-13T07:00:13.507031441Z","close_reason":"Completed: WebSocket::close now uses the explicit Cx timer source; added close_uses_explicit_cx_and_closes_on_peer_eof; rch cargo test and cargo check passed.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.346","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T06:50:34.840113849Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
-{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.347","title":"[audit][raptorq] Align send_object oversize guard with byte-based max_block_size contract","description":"RaptorQ sender-side oversized-data validation currently diverges from the encoder/decoder contract when encoding.symbol_size != 256. EncodingConfig documents max_block_size as bytes, and src/encoding.rs plus src/decoding.rs both enforce total object size as max_block_size * (u8::MAX + 1) bytes (bounded by 8-bit SBN space). But src/raptorq/pipeline.rs send_object and its tests multiply max_block_size by symbol_size instead, which rejects valid payloads early for symbol_size < 256 and allows oversized payloads through to lower-layer InvalidEncodingParams failures for symbol_size > 256. Scope: align sender precheck/tests to the byte-based contract and add focused regressions for non-256 symbol sizes so caller-visible ErrorKind stays correct.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"WhiteSnow","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:13:17.250195986Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T07:13:17.250195986Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.347","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:13:17.250195986Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.347","title":"[audit][raptorq] Align send_object oversize guard with byte-based max_block_size contract","description":"RaptorQ sender-side oversized-data validation currently diverges from the encoder/decoder contract when encoding.symbol_size != 256. EncodingConfig documents max_block_size as bytes, and src/encoding.rs plus src/decoding.rs both enforce total object size as max_block_size * (u8::MAX + 1) bytes (bounded by 8-bit SBN space). But src/raptorq/pipeline.rs send_object and its tests multiply max_block_size by symbol_size instead, which rejects valid payloads early for symbol_size < 256 and allows oversized payloads through to lower-layer InvalidEncodingParams failures for symbol_size > 256. Scope: align sender precheck/tests to the byte-based contract and add focused regressions for non-256 symbol sizes so caller-visible ErrorKind stays correct.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"WhiteSnow","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:13:17.250195986Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T07:58:57.391992476Z","closed_at":"2026-03-13T07:58:57.391966968Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.347","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T07:13:17.250195986Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
